This paper is about differential privacy for SQL queries, which is a topic related to databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses limitations of previous approaches and proposes a novel method for approximating local sensitivity, which are topics related to cryptography (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The empirical study conducted in the paper involves analyzing a large dataset of real-world queries, which is a topic related to data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper presents a practical system for enforcing differential privacy, which is a topic related to cybersecurity (cs.CY).
